---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="CIBIL Score Check by PAN Card | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/pages/credit-score">Credit Score</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>CIBIL Score Check by PAN</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Check CIBIL Score by <span class="gradient-text">PAN Card</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Instantly check your CIBIL score online using your PAN card number. Get a comprehensive credit report with score analysis and improvement recommendations.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-clock"></i>
          <span>Check Time: 2 Minutes</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-chart-simple"></i>
          <span>Score Range: 300–900</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-shield-halved"></i>
          <span>Impact: Zero</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">

          <!-- Overview -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Overview</span>
              <h2>What is CIBIL Score Check by PAN?</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Your PAN (Permanent Account Number) card is the primary identifier used by TransUnion CIBIL to link your credit history. Since every loan, credit card, and financial transaction reported to CIBIL is tagged to your PAN, it serves as the most reliable way to look up your CIBIL score accurately.</p>
            <p>When you check your CIBIL score using your PAN card through TrueCred, we securely verify your identity and fetch your credit report directly from CIBIL's database. This is classified as a "soft inquiry," meaning it has absolutely no impact on your credit score — you can check as many times as you want.</p>
            <p>Your CIBIL score ranges from 300 to 900, with 750+ considered excellent. The report includes your score, active credit accounts, repayment history, credit utilisation, outstanding balances, and any negative marks such as defaults or late payments.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Why PAN is Required -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Why PAN?</span>
              <h2>Why is PAN Card Required for CIBIL Check?</h2>
            </div>
            <p>The PAN card plays a critical role in India's credit reporting infrastructure. Understanding why it's essential helps you appreciate the accuracy and security of the process.</p>
            <table class="rate-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Factor</th>
                  <th>With PAN Card</th>
                  <th>Without PAN Card</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Identity Verification</strong></td>
                  <td>Instant & accurate</td>
                  <td>Manual & time-consuming</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Credit History Linking</strong></td>
                  <td>All accounts linked automatically</td>
                  <td>May miss linked accounts</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Report Accuracy</strong></td>
                  <td>100% comprehensive report</td>
                  <td>Partial or incomplete data</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Processing Time</strong></td>
                  <td>Under 2 minutes</td>
                  <td>3–7 business days</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Fraud Protection</strong></td>
                  <td>Strong (PAN-Aadhaar linked)</td>
                  <td>Weak verification</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Dispute Filing</strong></td>
                  <td>Directly via PAN reference</td>
                  <td>Requires additional documents</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <!-- Features -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Features</span>
              <h2>What You Get in Your CIBIL Report</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Your CIBIL report fetched via PAN card contains detailed financial information compiled from banks, NBFCs, and financial institutions across India. Here's what each section covers.</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Credit Score (300–900)</strong>
                  <p>Your three-digit CIBIL score calculated based on your credit behaviour. Scores above 750 are considered excellent and unlock the best loan and credit card offers.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Active Loan & Credit Card Accounts</strong>
                  <p>Complete list of all open credit accounts including personal loans, home loans, car loans, credit cards, and overdraft facilities with current balances and EMI details.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Repayment History (36 Months)</strong>
                  <p>Month-by-month payment track record for all accounts over the last 3 years. Shows on-time payments, late payments, and missed EMIs with exact dates.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Credit Utilisation Ratio</strong>
                  <p>Percentage of your available credit limit currently in use. A utilisation ratio below 30% is optimal and signals responsible credit management to lenders.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Hard & Soft Inquiry Records</strong>
                  <p>Details of every credit inquiry made by lenders (hard inquiries) and self-checks (soft inquiries) over the past 24 months, with dates and institution names.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Negative Marks & Defaults</strong>
                  <p>Any defaults, write-offs, settlements, or accounts sent to collections are flagged here. These stay on your report for up to 7 years and significantly impact your score.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Steps to Check -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Step by Step</span>
              <h2>How to Check CIBIL Score Using PAN Card</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Follow these simple steps to check your CIBIL score instantly using your PAN card. The entire process takes less than 2 minutes and is completely free on TrueCred.</p>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <h3>Enter PAN Details</h3>
                <p>Enter your full name exactly as printed on your PAN card, followed by your 10-character PAN number. Ensure there are no typos as the system validates against government records.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <h3>Verify Your Identity</h3>
                <p>Enter your registered mobile number and date of birth. An OTP will be sent to your mobile for secure identity verification before accessing your credit data.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <h3>View Your CIBIL Score</h3>
                <p>Your CIBIL score and full credit report are displayed instantly. Review your score, active accounts, repayment history, and any negative marks on your profile.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">4</div>
                <h3>Download & Take Action</h3>
                <p>Download a PDF copy of your credit report. If you spot errors, initiate a dispute directly. Get personalised recommendations to improve your score and access better offers.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">

          <!-- Check Score Form -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-id-card"></i> Check CIBIL by PAN</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="PAN Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="date" class="form-input" placeholder="Date of Birth" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Check CIBIL Score <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
              <p class="form-disclaimer">
                <i class="fas fa-lock"></i> 100% safe & secure. No impact on your score.
              </p>
            </form>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Links -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <ul class="sidebar-links">
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Free Credit Score</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/increase-cibil-score"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Increase CIBIL Score</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/cibil-score-personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> CIBIL for Personal Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/cibil-score-credit-card"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> CIBIL for Credit Card</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/cibil-dispute"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Raise CIBIL Dispute</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Personal Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Credit Cards</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> EMI Calculators</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About CIBIL Score Check by PAN</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I check my CIBIL score for free using my PAN card?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes, you can check your CIBIL score for free using your PAN card on TrueCred. CIBIL also allows one free report per year through their official website. On TrueCred, there is no limit — you can check your score as many times as you want at zero cost, and it counts as a soft inquiry that doesn't affect your score.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What if my PAN card name doesn't match my bank records?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>If there is a name mismatch between your PAN card and bank records, the CIBIL check may fail or show an incomplete report. In such cases, you should first update your name with either the Income Tax department (for PAN) or your bank to ensure consistency. Once the records match, you can successfully fetch your complete credit report.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Is it safe to enter my PAN number online?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes, it is safe to enter your PAN number on TrueCred. We use 256-bit SSL encryption and are ISO 27001 certified. Your PAN is transmitted securely and used solely for identity verification with CIBIL. We do not store your PAN number after the verification process, and your data is never shared with third parties without your explicit consent.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Why does my CIBIL report show "No Record Found" with a valid PAN?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>A "No Record Found" result means CIBIL has no credit history associated with your PAN. This typically happens if you've never taken a loan, never had a credit card, or your lenders haven't reported your accounts to CIBIL yet. In such cases, you can build your credit history by taking a secured credit card or a small personal loan and ensuring timely repayments.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>How often should I check my CIBIL score using PAN?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>It's recommended to check your CIBIL score at least once every quarter (every 3 months) to stay on top of your credit health. Additionally, check your score before applying for any loan or credit card, after closing a loan account, or if you suspect any fraudulent activity. Regular monitoring helps you catch errors early and track the impact of your financial decisions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Check Your CIBIL Score by PAN Card Now</h2>
      <p>Get your free CIBIL report in just 2 minutes using your PAN card. Completely safe, no hidden charges, zero impact on your score.</p>
      <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
        Check CIBIL Score <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
